  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And will make an offering by fire unto the Lord, a burnt offering,.... The first of these respects such offerings by fire, which were not wholly burnt, but part of them were eaten by the priests, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 18:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and the latter such as were wholly burnt, unless the latter can be thought to be only an explanation of the former: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or a sacrifice in performing a vow, or in a freewill offering; these were peace offerings, some of which were for thanksgiving, and others were either a vow or a freewill offering, as here: see Leviticus 7:11, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "or a sacrifice in performing a vow, or in a freewill offering; these were peace offerings, some of which were for thanksgiving, and others were either a vow or a freewill offering, as here: see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 7:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or in your solemn feasts; as the passover, pentecost, &c. of which, and the offerings in them, see Leviticus 23:4, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "or in your solemn feasts; as the passover, pentecost, &c. of which, and the offerings in them, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 23:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to make a sweet savour unto the Lord; for acceptance with him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of the herd or of the flock; a bullock of the one, a lamb or kid of the goats of the other; fowls are not mentioned, because burnt offerings of them required no drink offerings (f). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(f) Maimon. Maaseh Hakorbanot, c. 2. sect. 2.",
